{
  "texts": [
    "We extracted contextualized word embeddings from GPT-2 using the Hugging Face environment 65.",
    "We first converted the words from the raw transcript (including punctuation and capitalization) to tokens comprising whole words or sub-words (e.g., there's → there's).",
    "We used a sliding window of 1024 tokens, moving one token at a time, to extract the embedding for the final word in the sequence (i.e., the word and its history).",
    "We extracted the activity of the final hidden layer of GPT-2 (which has 48 hidden layers).",
    "The contextual embedding of a word is the activity of the last hidden layer given all the words up to and not including the word of interest (in GPT-2, the word is predicted using the last hidden state)."
  ]
}